PCE RAG, redaction, and store discipline.

Never bypass the redaction/chunking pipeline for user or system data. All retrieval and generation must go through the established redaction and chunking stages, not ad-hoc queries over raw data.

Prefer existing orchestration primitives for retrieval and generation instead of inventing new flows. Extend or compose the current PCE RAG orchestration patterns before adding new pipelines.

Treat stores (history, traces, tool executions, and similar) as internal contracts. Do not advise direct database access, schema poking, or manual migrations for these; use the established store APIs and patterns.

For logging and metrics, keep metric names consistent with existing conventions and cardinality expectations. Avoid adding noisy or low-signal logs and metrics without a clear purpose and consumer.

